76561198007682607,Not Recommended,272270,31116579,Posted: 13 April,all,Sicko,"I can't reccomend this and I can't willingly motivate myself to keep playing this game. There is more than enough well written reviews of this game so I won't bother repeating a great deal of what has already been said about the short falls and issues.*Have since played another 3 hours on a friends account and its only reinforced my initial perspective...The main reason I'm dropping this game already, less than 5 hours of play in, is because it just doesn't hit the mark to stand with the legacy of Planescape Torment. The atmosphere and asthetic elements are just not right, too much flashy sci fi styles spilling into the gameworld of TTON (lasers, facial augmentation machines etc). The asthetics are just off; there are points in the city which will feel similar to the city of Sigil from Planescape Torment but there is too many other graphics and designs that just don't fit. The combat is horrible; slow, contrived and a constant feeling of playing through scripted battles (removing real rpg aspects we enjoy; grinding, leveling, stats, looting). The Tides/Skill interface is clanky and slow; bringing nothing really significant to the game that I felt validated a need for this system at all. From the start onwards the dialogue is just dull and fails to immerse me into this world. I found no vested interests in my characters plight or the party members who joined me, besides Rhin. The character creation system is interesting but felt like it makes next to no difference in general with how events and quests play out (and come on, no option to chose a potrait - stuck with some bland face that looks like it came from a 1970's Sci Fi novel cover). I think that by focussing on being a dialogue/text heavy game too much the developers have ultimately failed to incorporate typical RPG elements that made the original game so good - we've got this unbalanced result of a game that has turned into a very linear. almost point and click adventure game. Big dissapointment.There is moments, glimmers of good writing and creativity, where this game shows some potential I found in a few of the side quests. But these moments are over shadowed by the points I made above.Look forward to modders ripping this game apart and rebuilding it into something the Torment community wants. I feel for the backers who got screwed over here but hopefully update patches can fix some of these issues. Save your cash and buy the Enchanced Edition of Planescape Torment or check out many of the other recent RPG's like Tyranny, Pillars etc"
