,Recommended,272270,30323618,Posted: 4 March,all,Sapidus,"So there IS a lot of problems with this game. In particular depending on why you like CRPGs you might hate this. I did not back this on Kickstarter, so can't speak to that. I can say that it feels like a complete game.However, I loved it.If you like tactical combat, and that is what draws you to CRPS, avoid this. The combat is ""eh"" (mainly because I feel like everything is so slow). Depending on how you play, there also is not a lot of it.For example, you can talk or think your way around most combat. I think I only had 5 or 6 combats in my playthrough, and they were ""crisis"" where the victory was not ""kill everyone"" (or at least the only victory), but instead had alternate win conditions.Honestly, I found it super refreshing. You don't often see that in a game.It has an interesting world with an interesting plot. Some of the interactions were really good. One of the party members is up there as favorite party member in any game.Time wise you can probably get through the main quest pretty quickly. However, playing through and exploring and taking your time will probably give you 30-40 hours.HOWEVER,The game does kinda look not so great. If you zoom in the graphics actually look much better (not the character models though. They are aweful). But I like to play more zoomed out, and it just does not look great.I would have also loved to have character portriates while talking to NPCs.I did not run into a lot of bugs, at least until the end. I experienced some loading problems that made it hard to complete the game.TL;DRIf you like character development and exploration, don't mind a lack of combat, and don't mind reading, I highly recomend this game."
