76561198158149244,Not Recommended,272270,30247410,Posted: 28 February,all,tuckboat,It's a strange and gorgeous world torn right out of a good sci-fi or fantasy novel and the game's mechanics complement the story and setting quite nicely.Obviously not an action title and the turn based combat is enjoyable enough in small doses here and there. I would put the writing up there with just about anything I've ever played before.Combat is mediocre but enjoyable enough if you like turn-based rpgs. Really you are here for the story and the intersting tidal pool system of progressing through challenges (won't go into detail here).It's good. Really good. Not sure if it's great yet but I have high hopes. I would say it's already been worth the price of admission and I am only about 10 hours in (maybe 1/4- 1/3 of the way through I am guessing).Update....erghhh. Changing my recommendation. It's pretty clear the first 1/3 of the game was done with level of production and the middle third or so a good step down in quality from that with the end of it feeling like a rushed mess.The main story (and it's very linear game if you were curious) in a vacum is just good enough to get a nod of approval. However it needed to be eleveated by other aspects of gameplay and writing in order to resonate and fails to do so mainly because the main character winds up being a half-user choice created personality (you pick'em) with the other half of that personality being a block of wood. Some games/stories get passed this hurdle by providing strong supporting characters with a ton of personality or a really good antagonist whom drives the plot forward. Well here the story of your side characters fails to evolve into anything of much interest past the first 1/3 and the antagonist was nothign to write home about. The bad guy I found to be somewhat interesting in concept but again just not good enough without any character to draw the player. Overall the lore is great and stays pretty strong up until the last hour or so of the game. The prose is gold standard other games should reach for but ultimatley the story falls well short of the mark it would need to completely carry the game.The turn-based battles become more tedious and harder to avoid towards the end of the game. It really hurts the experience and it felt unbalanced and poorly planned out by the end of the game. The skills system is pretty easy to overpower once you reach the half way point of the story with a decent amoutn of time spent on sidequest which sees it's early potential squandered.  Tactical considerations are not terrible important to your success as long as you have a decent character setup.Artwise it's a mixed bag here. The enviornments are well thought out and put together. Only a few maps (particularly towards the end) fail to impress. On the other hand the character models are pretty vanilla imo. The style of the armor/clothing on some of the major models are fairly well done but alot of the others are barely distinguishable from one another and while never terrible failed to impress and became a let down compared to the background/map artwork.So in the end we have a lore-rich interesting sci-fi shell and intro that is cause for alot of excitement and then the game just kind of slumps along without direction until it devolves into a really huge disappointment in the last few hours. This is the biggest implosion after a promising start to a game since...well Wasteland 2 probably. Not a good trend for this developer and I'm really sad to have to give this a thumbs down.4.5/10
