76561198009778179,Recommended,272270,31873488,Posted: 20 May,all,Kyl Von Kull,"This game deserves a lot more credit than it's getting.  Once I started playing, I couldn't stop.  The writing is amazing, as is the setting.  And let's be honest, if you loved the original Planescape: Torment, it's because it had great writing with an insanely immersive world.  Numenera feels shorter because there's very little combat (before this game, I never realized quite how much even the best CRPGs relied on combat to fluff things up), but it's VERY immersive.  If you loved the old '90s RPGs this hails back to, then you will almost definitely enjoy compulsively exploring Numenera.  If you miss RPGs with odd stories and walls of text, you will enjoy Numenera.An excellent game that would get much better reviews if it was a standalone title rather than being marketed as the spiritual sequel to the best game ever made."
