xplained by, we are castoffs we're special.so lets say the Changing god has been around for a thousand years, which he hasnt as it is stated that he started this practise after the tabaht conflict which was a few hundred years ago in the game. So they also say he changes every decade or so. lets be generous and give him 500 years. At a castoff per decade thats 50 cast offs. So he would have had to be over 3000 years old to have around 300 castoffs. A lot of which are dead/disappeared. So the Sorrow, this extradimensional being is summoned into existence for, at an absolute max 300 people? Over 3000 years? That have affected a tiny portion of the world and made it sad? Not buying it. Should have just made a cool canonical numenera game.Basically this game follows the plot of throne of bhaal/shadows of amn.why does every game you guys make have to be about gods and changing the world/universe?? You know most rpg people would be happy with more freedom over character origin/backstory and a main quest that was about the land you are in specifically, you know factions, politics who you work for etc an just that, but well done and fleshed out. Not always, I am the chosen one, I must know myself/find my creator/mysterious scientist man/god who is bothering/hunting me. Its like the hero's journey on steroids, every time.If you are going to make a game out of existing IP then why not use that IP and lore that worked so well? Why invent new areas/factions/really big important reasons? if you already have lore and history that not only works a lot better and has had way more time to be improved and refined but you have also paid for the rights to, then why oh why would you recreate the same story you have told with other IP in this universe? I suspect that there is someone within your team that is like, let's make a difference guys, let's change people's perspectives, let's enlighten people. Yet instead of doing those things you are forcefeeding us the same ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥t karmic/universal/finding yourself story in different formats. We are not looking for games like this to enlighten us or make us better people, there are plenty of opportunities in the modern age for access to material that is much more profound and likely to affect us than a Crpg. Please just stick to making good games and stop trying to affect us spiritually, it is incredibly boring and done in a really amateurish way.All in all this game has all the elements to be truly great. I am hoping that a decent amount of time is spent on making some great DLC to really open it up and give us a more exploratory/self created adventure."
