76561198217069788,Recommended,272270,30104793,Posted: 22 February,all,Peace of Mind,"To anyone comming here with a open mind looking foward to buy this game: a LOT o people gave this game bad reviews based on the fact that they promissed a unpause-pause battle mode which they changed to a turn-based. While the complains are legit, it DOES NOT reflect the quality of the game itself (they will probably also thumbs down this review to death too).The game has a really good narrative, voice acting and dialogues. Your choices matters a lot. I liked the way you do notdirectly customize your character. Instead, the choices you make on the start of the games customize your character for you (and you can not change it).I have not yet finished the game, but I already feel attracted to its lore and envolving atmosphere. I feel like I want to know story and that the protagonist I control is really myself and not a 3rd person.The fight system is a turn-based and rely on your primary attributes: might, speed and intellect. You have points on these attributes which is spent during the fight. The amount of max points on each attributes varies on the caracter creation. These points can also be used to easy your way on the storyline (like ""etiquette"" on Shadowrun). In some situations, like a dialogue, you can use might points to intimate the person you're talking to, the more points you spend, the higher is the chance to have a succesful outcome.The flaws on this game relies on the fact that theres not a quest ticker on the map/mini-map like many RPGs (espcially open-worlds), which i think it would make the game flow easier for people with avarage english (like myself) who do not completly understand those well-written texts. Thats a small feature which I miss a lot.Overall, I'd give the game a 9/10."
