76561198041170112,Recommended,272270,30662633,Posted: 21 March,all,Moller_Khan,"This is an old-school RPG with all of the pros of 90s gaming - high on ideas and low on fluff.Some of the complaints here are totally unjustified, money-driven and give you a huge sense of how entitled gamers have become. For the record, Planescape: Torment was also 40 Euros/Pounds/Dollars back in the '90s.Torment: Tides of Numenera is an immersive experience that expands your mind, confronts you with hundreds of philosophical questions and makes you look at morality in a completely different way. InXile should be applauded because this is the first RPG I actually could stomach for a long time. There have been a lot of saccharine, stupid games in the genre over the last 15 years and the imagination that went into this game is a feat in itself.If you want epilepsy inducing 4k graphics, non-stop killing and brainless clicking, look elsewhere. This is a game that demands your absolute attention, logic and abstract imagination. Torment: Tides of Numenera has the same undeniable quality, weirdness and presence that PS:T had... except it's not Planescape, the combat is turn-based and it's a bit short.Pros:- Some of the best game writing in a long time.- You can think or talk your way out of any situation.- The Crisis system is an inventive take on turn-based combat.- The graphics are a great nod to the original Torment.- Excellent soundtrack. Dark, atmospheric, ambient.- The meres: mini-stories that allow you to influence the game.- Forces you to think critically.- Numenera's Tides System is a new take on morality - all of it is relative.- Beautiful, weird and downright disgusting locations.- The visuals and animation breathe new life into the isometric RPG format.- Items can help or harm you and all of them are odd.- The sheer number of options and outcomes make it very replayable.- Totally alien and dystopian: free of shouty 21st century politics.(potential) Cons:- Shorter than expected.- No faction system.- Very text heavy. If you don't like reading, don't buy it.- Not for zombies. Requires imagination.- There are some minor bugs in the current version.- Some very blatant re-hashes of the original Torment.- Small choice of characters."
