76561197970001035,Recommended,272270,34509000,Posted: 26 August,all,SirZerator,"An excellent game, set in a very enticing universe ! I highly recommend it to anyone who likes good story-telling.Numenera invites you to explore a weird and unknown world, playing as a character who doesn't know much and can't understand fully what's happening to him/her. Although the combat system is a little complicated at first (you get used to it), most of the game is not really about fighting but more about exploration, dialogue and decision-making. Every one of the decisions you make will have an influence on the world, the people you meet and yourself. Some of them minor and some very significant.It's really interesting that in many situations, you don't fully understand what's happening, what you're supposed to do or just what is the right thing to do. Remember PS: Torment, waking up in the morgue, greeted by a talking, floating skull, go meet that guy you never heard about before... well, that's the feeling.The places you explore couldn't be more alien, yet with a little bit of familiarity. I like the fact that the technology you encounter is so new, so advanced and sophisticated, it almost looks like magic (Clarke's third law right there)."
76561198017043455,Recommended,272270,30369055,Posted: 7 March,all,Halicron,"What an awesome game.Please buy this game. Support these kind of classic RPGs. It's a dying art, this gaming medium of interactive storytelling. When you use your dollars to show your support, you help the writers and developers know that their work is appreciated and desired.This game is frustrating. It's frustrating in the best of ways. It's frustrating in that you can't outsmart it every time. You will make mistakes. But mistakes are OK! Mistakes sometimes lead to opportunities you wouldn't have had otherwise. Failure isn't always the end. Sometimes it's the beginning.This game is meant to challenge you. Don't savescum for best options. Accept that you'll make mistakes. Burn through your limited resources. But talk to -everyone-. So many people have a story. So many of them might have some hidden secret for you.I think that's what I loved best about this, was digging through the small secrets and finding big ones. The characters were fun and interesting to play with, the setting was weird and alien and macabre and funny-- it reminded me so much of the original Torment, a game with such a weirdly alien setting that no one should feel 'comfortable' there. You will fulfill and subvert tropes almost constantly.This game isn't a challenge to be summited. It's a story to be read-- an experienced to be shared."
