76561198012067179,Recommended,272270,34404388,Posted: 21 August,all,jorgonq,"This is one of the best, most original games I've played in recent memory. To start, my very small list of gripes:The ending: I felt the ending was a little lackluster. I loved the revelation of a large chunk of the plot however, I felt the end decisions were too open-ended. I would much prefer to be forced into only a couple of decisions via my choice-making throughtout the game.Length: I felt the game was too short. I accomplished the vast majority of tasks in my first play through and spent about 30 hours total. This game is so great I just want more of it.Equipment: I love inventory management and felt that there weren't enough weapon and armor choices.What I did loveThe World: The Ninth World is super cool. I love the mix of ancient, decaying tech with limited magic, some divine interference, and a splash of high-fantasy. If a sequel is made I hope it utilizes this same world with its rich history.Combat: I love that, especially in the beginning, the use of ability points is soooo agonizing. It makes every decision feel very important and also challenges the player to think outside the box and try to use the environment around them.The Story: Very fun and interesting story. I felt each chapter did a good job of fleshing out my character and what he/she was. I daresay by the end I actually cared about my character, which rarely happens.Environmental Interactions: It felt like nearly every other thing could be interacted with, and, most importantly, if a skill check failed it wasn't a big deal because sometimes something even better happened as a result.In summation, if you enjoy story driven games with inventive combat and good environmental interaction this game is for you."
