,Recommended,272270,33758663,Posted: 23 July,all,napoleonic_sp007rz,"Maybe not as good as the original but still pretty good on it's own+ bizarre interesting background world that blend scifi with fantasy although overall the game take side to fantasy more than scifi (opposite of mass effect, for example, but this world is much much more bizarre).+ effort system, this system let you capable of trying harder to pass a skill check on many action both in and out of combat at the expense of your effort pool points, for example a normal attack with no extra effort cost you 0 effort point but only has 55% chance of hit while dealing 5 damage, if you spend 1 effort point that would add 10% chance to hit and +1 damage but of course your effort point on that area decreased by 1 point until the next rest.+ effort system isn't limited to combat, you have options to do so on any other actions including conversation (on specific occasions of course) and interacting with the world, IMO this is a gamechanger on rpg and a must have for any other rpg, I hope devs start adding it, after all oit add potential for role playing.+ more meaningful loots compared in other rpgs, as the dev said, there is no generic mace +1 damage as loot in this game, instead even the weakest loot has some interesting effect on this game.+/- hand crafted encounters with option to solve it in numerous ways including non combat for almost all encounters in the game, that mean there is no random trash mob fights in this game, I like it but some may not.+ with bizarre world comes bizarre characters- mediocre turn based combat- end game not as satisfying as the beginning.- although the world and characters are more bizarre here, I'm liking tyranny's characters/companions more, they are more memorable there than here, not realy sure myself why, maybe because the bizarre game world itself overshadow your companions here.- I hoped it would havre been more on the scifi thing than fantasy."
