76561198047855705,Recommended,272270,32259015,Posted: 7 June,all,jordanl.l300,"I have 70 hours in on this game. in a SINGLE playthrough. This game was pure CRPG refinement. This is a masterfully done throwback to the artistic story driven games of legend.But enough about my opinion.The facts:If you don't like reading the game is lost on you. Not saying you cant expedite dialogue choices, but as the sequel to Planescape: Torment the game expands exponentially when you embrace the dialogue. There are even multiple choose your own mini adventures in the form of ""merecasters"" throughout the game which are, for the most part optional.Combat is a lot of fun. There are many choices to be made which affect your resolution of ""crisis"" which can be done through guile or firepower.The story is extremely well written. Definitely feels like the games of old, as I said. I found myself very enthralled and very engrossed in the story above and beyond the combat. Hungry and curious for exposing all the secrets and mysteies of the Ninth World and beyond.Be seduced by extra-planar entities. Playing for the paragon? Find yourself mystified and enthralled by a giant fleshy predator that approves or disproves your choices. Slowly corrupting you to more predatory actions.A completely alien world very unique lore and lots and lots of subtexts to help give you a large and living picture of this world a billion years in the future.Extremely fun and well worth the read/playthrough."
