76561198080355090,Recommended,272270,30260040,Posted: 1 March,all,MFMegaZeroX,"Despite what many of the top reviews are saying right now, this game is fantastic. The negative reviews are mainly for a mismanaged Kickstarter. So long as you aren't part of that, then this outrage doesn't effect you.The actual game itself is a very well written spiritual successor to Planescape Torment. However, there is even less of an emphasis on combat, so if you prefer more combat heavy RPGs like Baldur's Gate than this may not be for you.The RPG mechanical elements themselves are pretty light. There are 3 ""effort"" skills you can spend to pass checks, which can only be recharged by items and sleeping. The combat is also based on spending these skills to use abilities.The main alluring part of this RPG is the top quality writing and all of the different choices that can be made during quests and even outside of quests. For example, in many quests, you have the ability to learn deep secrets from people. After finishing the quest, you could always go and trade those secrets away for another secret, perhaps one that can save people, or perhaps one that you can use to your advantage. Is this something you want to do?Torment: Tides of Numenara is all about these kinds of choices. If this sounds appealing to you, then I highly recommend the game!"
