,Recommended,272270,30752335,Posted: 26 March,all,Peppery Rabbit,"I played this game after going back and completing Planescape: Torment and, honestly, it's very very loosely attached to it. The only things that a taken from that are a few vague themes. I'm not complaining about that at all because this game stands up on its own.As with every game like this, the main upsides are going to be the story and the characters. The characters and their development were done very well. Each person has their own unique feel and you do genuinely get drawn into their own stories, none moreso (for me) that Rhin.The story, on the other hand, was pretty bare bones but I feel it was more a vehicle for the characters and it was interesting to a point.The look of the game is also great, lending a lot to the themes and the different ages of history that you're told about. The cyphers and esoteries (spells) are also quite cool and well animated.Now for a few gripes I had. Firstly, the voice acting. The quality itself was fine, as you would expect from a higher budget indie game but the amount was quite disappointing. You expect to have voice acting all along the main storyline in games like this but, even when you would expect it, it wasn't there. For example, the last encounter of the game had no voice acting.Secondly, there is A LOT of text. I feel like these 2 points are linked but I feel this would turn off a lot of people.Finally, the combat mechanics were a bit poor. I feel like it would have benefited from a system with disengaging strikes and other things from the game Tyranny.Overall, it's a great, interesting game with a hell of a lot of character and you can just tell the devs loved making it.If you like story, grab it. If you like old school CRPGs, why haven't you already got it?"
76561198070919265,Recommended,272270,31332220,Posted: 23 April,all,jastick,"The world is engaging and the characters are interesting I happily emursed myself in the game world exploring the deep history and interesting resource system. The combat for the most part isn't very challenging or interesting and lacks most strategic depth with certain attacks and abilites being obviously better in almost every situation. Having said that I still enjoyed it, and the process of trying to manage your resources in combat so you still have something to work with to complete tasks felt added a slight tactical wrinkle. (Having said that with solid character building that can be all but eliminated.) The focus of this game is story, and building an interesting setting and exploring ideas, I believe it succeeded on those fronts. As such I would recomend it to anyone interested in an interesting and engaging story and game world."
