76561198013336701,Not Recommended,272270,30436800,Posted: 10 March,all,TinEater,"My first reaction to this game was crazy positive.  I'm an old-school RPG guy and it checks off all of my boxes.  Unfortunately, it's sitting on my hard drive unfinished and unplayed for months.I just don't feel compelled to go back to it.  Why?  I don't mind text-walls but there's very little game-play outside of the dialogue boxes.  The writing is meant to be the big draw of the game, but it's wildly overwritten.  It aims for flavorful but ends up being obtuse, even pretentious.  The density of the text also makes re-starting feel like a slog.  And you will re-start.  Character choices, both in the beginning and at advancement, aren't meaningfully explained, and there's no respec option (to my knowledge). The infrequent combats feel more like puzzles than fights.  It's is the only respite from Torment's relentless purple prose, but it's easilly the most irritating part of the game.While it's admirable that this game is trying to do something different, the end result just isn't fun."
